==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} {{term|billion|lang=fr}}. From the prefix ''[[bi-]]'', meaning ''two'' + ''[[-illion]]'' (from [[million]]); [[i.e.]] a [[million]] [[million]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈbɪljən/}}, {{SAMPA|/"bIlj@n/}}
* {{audio|en-us-billion.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪljən}}
* {{hyphenation|bil|lion}}

===Cardinal number===
{{enum|million|trillion|cardinal number|10<sup>9</sup>}}
{{enum|milliard|billiard|cardinal number|10<sup>12</sup>}}
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|US|modern British & Australian|[[w:Long and short scales|short scale]]}} A [[milliard]], a [[thousand]] [[million]]: 1 followed by nine zeros, 10<sup>9</sup>.
# {{context|obsolete British & Australian|[[w:Long and short scales|long scale]]}} A [[million]] [[million]]: a 1 followed by twelve zeros, 10<sup>12</sup>.
# {{context|colloquial|plural}} A very large number.
#: ''There were billions of people at the concert''

